INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (2, 'New_Material_Carbon_Nanotube_Test_Report_2', '2019-01-08 16:57:56', NULL, 1045, 62, 0, '  <p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-27/Carbon Nanotube02.png\" alt=\"pcb  prototype\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<h3>About heat transportation and insulation</h3>\n<p>In the electronics industry, there are many kinds of PCB materials, they all have advantages and disadvantages, for example,&nbsp; FR4 is good insulation but poor heat transportation, and Aluminum or Copper base is good heat transportation but poor insulation. In this case, a new material appears, and it is&nbsp; Carbon Nanotube. Let\'s verify it through an experiment.</p>\n<h3>The experimental material is 30W Dimmable LED Light</h3>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/654.png\" alt=\"pcbonline\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>Test Parameters: heat transportation &amp; Insulation. 220V input dimming, heat transportation, and insulation are very important.</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/04.png\" alt=\"PCB ONLINE\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>Nano-coating Test: Voltage:500V &amp; 200V</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/05.png\" alt=\"Aluminum Board\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/07.png\" alt=\"PCB Assembly\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/06.png\" alt=\"cheap pcb\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>Insulation Test:Voltage:1.5KV ,Electricity:1.0mA-100mA,Test Time: 1 Sec</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/10.png\" alt=\"Low Cost PCB\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/08.png\" alt=\"PCB Quote\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/09.png\" alt=\"PCB Manufacturer\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>Temperature Test:</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/11.png\" alt=\"PCB Fabrication\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>CNT Board：63℃</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-15/12.png\" alt=\"PCB prototype\">\n    <br>\n</p>\n<p>Aluminum Board：84℃</p>\n<p>\n    <span style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n        <br>\n    </span>\n</p>  ', 'PCB Technology', 1, 2, 2, NULL, NULL, 'Carbon Nanotube Test Report - PCB fabrication', 'Low Cost PCB, PCB Manufacturer, pcb prototyping ', 'Our company has passed UL certificates，ISO9001, ISO14001, and SGS. 100% reliable PCBs. You can get instant Order PCB Online.', 0, '2019-03-23 13:01:56', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (3, 'Carbon_Nanotube_material_used_in_PCB_---_New_Technology_3', '2019-01-08 18:31:42', NULL, 510, 25, 1, '<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-03-23/PCB%20prototype.png\" alt=\"PCB prototype.png\"> <br>\n</p>\n<h2>Carbon Nanotube</h2>\n<p>Carbon nanotubes, with their extraordinary mechanical and unique electronic properties, have garnered much attention in the past five years. With a broad range of potential applications including nanoelectronics, composites, chemical sensors, biosensors, microscopy, nanoelectromechanical systems, and many more, the scientific community is more motivated than ever to move beyond basic properties and explore the real issues associated with carbon nanotube-based applications.</p>\n<p>\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-27/Carbon%20Nanotube002.jpg\" alt=\"pcb  prototype\"> <br>\n</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\n    <span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The manufacturer -&nbsp;</span>Yugu&nbsp;Chemical&nbsp;Material Ltd.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Our<span> subsidiary \"Yugu</span> Chemical<span></span> <span>M</span><span>aterial&nbsp;</span><span>Ltd.</span> <span>\"</span> <span>&nbsp;</span> <span>located in</span> &nbsp;<span>Shenzhen, has successfully developed a material that can completely replace the high-conductivity aluminum substrate and has been successfully mass-produced.</span> <span>&nbsp;</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-03-23/222222222.jpg\" alt=\"gold finger\">\n</p>\n<h2>Composition: Aluminum + carbon nanotube</h2>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">\n    <span>Due to the</span> <span>cellular</span> <span>structure and the chemical properties of carbon,</span> Carbon<span></span> <span>Nanotube</span> <span>material has the characteristics of fast heat, high-temperature resistance, anti-static, light weight and resistance to chemical</span> attack.<span></span> &nbsp;Because<span> the</span> Carbon Nanotube material does<span> not have the conductivity,</span> <span>It perfectly solves the problem that double-sided aluminum substrate needs to do \"</span> <span>T</span><span>hermoelectric</span> Separation technology,<span></span> <span>which not only saves the production cost but also reduces the production difficulty.</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-03-23/1111.png\" alt=\"edge plating printed circuit board\">\n</p>\n<h2>PCB Board Test</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" align=\"justify\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n    <span>We have accurate test data to confirm that</span> Carbon<span></span> <span>Nanotube</span> <span>materials have far better performance than aluminum sheets in heat loss performance and</span> <span>poor</span> <span>working environment.</span> <span>&nbsp;</span> <span>Carbon</span> <span>Nanotube PCB</span> <span>&nbsp;excellent heat dissipation ability is dozens of times the aluminum</span> PCB,<span> thermal conductivity is about five times the aluminum</span> PCB.<span>&nbsp;</span> <span> </span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" align=\"justify\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n    <span>Under the influence of severe weather, such as outdoor storm, sea brine impact, lightning, etc.,</span> Carbon<span></span> <span>Nanotube</span> <span>PCB</span> <span>shows ultra-high stability and is not subject to damage and interference, while aluminum</span> <span>PCB</span> <span>is unsafe and easy to be corroded in the harsh working environment, and there are quality hidden dangers in long-term work.</span> <span> </span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    <img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-03-23/carbon-fiber-pcb-prototype-02.png\" alt=\"carbon-fiber-pcb-prototype\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n    <br>\n</p>', 'SMT', 1, 2, 2, 'zhangsan', NULL, 'Carbon Nanotube - PCB  New Technology', 'PCB manufacturer china, aluminum board, pcb assembly online quote', 'How to Order Cheap PCB， it is now very easy to get a ready PCB Online', 0, '2019-03-23 21:55:31', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (4, '520MM_FPC_-	Flexible_Printed_Circuit_4', '2019-01-08 18:58:08', NULL, 594, 20, 0, '      <p><img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-26/mix01.jpg\" alt=\"pcb  prototype\"><br></p><p>FPC, also known as \"Flexible Printed Circuit Board\", is a Printed Circuit made of Flexible insulating substrate, which has many advantages that hard Printed Circuit Board does not have. For example, it can be freely bent, wound and folded, and can be arranged arbitrarily according to the spatial layout requirements, and can be moved and expanded arbitrarily in the three-dimensional space, so as to achieve the integration of component assembly and wire connection.FPC flexible board can greatly reduce the volume of electronic products, which is suitable for the development of electronic products to high density, miniaturization, and high reliability. Therefore, FPC flexible board has been widely used in aerospace, military, mobile communication, laptop, computer peripherals, PDA, digital cameras and other fields or products.FPC flexible board also has the advantages of good heat dissipation and weldability, easy installation and connection, low comprehensive cost, etc. The design of soft and hard combination also makes up for the slight deficiency of flexible substrate in the bearing capacity of components to some extent. The flexible printed circuit board can be divided into single-sided, double-sided and multi-layer boards. The substrate used is polyimide copper clad sheet. This kind of material has high heat resistance, good dimensional stability, and the covering film with both mechanical protection and good electrical insulation performance is made by pressing the final product. The surface and inner conductors of the double-sided and multi-layer printed circuit board are metalized to realize the electrical connection of the inner and outer layers. The functions of FPC can be divided into four types, namely, Lead Line, Printed Circuit, Connector, and Integration of Function, which covers the use of computers, peripheral auxiliary systems, consumer electrical appliances and automobiles</p><p><img src=\"https://www.pcbonline.com/file/2019-01-26/3217.jpg\" alt=\"pcb  prototype\"></p><p>PCB prototype&nbsp;single size: 520*7.5mm</p><p>panel size: 520*240mm/32PCS</p><p>Material: FPC</p><p>Finish Thickness: 0.3mm</p><p>Layers: 2 Layer</p><p>Soldmask: white</p><p>silkscreen: green</p><p>Copper Thickness: 1oz</p><p><br></p>   ', 'PCB prototype ', 1, 2, 2, 'zhangsan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL);
